    "It can be summarized in the formula below:",
    "where L (y, p) is the loss for a single data point, y is the actual binary label (0 or 1), and p is the predicted probability that the data point belongs to class 1.",
    "Lower loss values for the discriminator indicate the discriminator's ability to differentiate between synthetic and real data while for the overall model, it indicates the generator's ability to fool the discriminator.",
